Two separate issues:

**1. `StaticResource` won't update at runtime.**
`StaticResource` resolves once at XAML load. Switch to `DynamicResource` so bindings re-evaluate when the dictionary changes:

```xml
<!-- ✗ won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✓ updates when theme changes -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing/merging dictionaries at runtime:

```csharp
// In your theme-toggle handler:
var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDictionaries.Clear();
mergedDictionaries.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

**2. Android restarts the `Activity` on UI-mode changes.**
By default, a `uiMode` configuration change (dark/light toggle) destroys and recreates the activity. Handle it yourself by adding `ConfigChanges` in your `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.Orientation
                         | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                         | ConfigChanges.UiMode,   // ← add this
    LaunchMode = LaunchMode.SingleTop)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
}
```

With `ConfigChanges.UiMode`, Android won't recreate the activity. You can then detect the change and apply your theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    // swap your ResourceDictionary here
}
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` everywhere you want live updates; add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to prevent the activity restart.
